# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# │      │          │
# │      │          └─ imperative, lower-case, no trailing period, ≤ 100 chars total
# │      └─ optional: security|networking|ui|auth|storage|agents|skills|workflows|
# │                   checklists|standards|architecture|prompts|templates|examples|ci|repo
# └─ feat|fix|docs|refactor|test|chore|perf|build|ci|revert
#
# (blank line, then the body — explain WHAT and WHY, wrap ~72 chars)
#
# (blank line, then footer — e.g. "Closes #123" or "BREAKING CHANGE: ...")
#
# Example:
#   feat(security): add public-key TLS pinning with backup pin
#
#   Concurrent 401s previously triggered multiple refreshes. Serialize refresh
#   through an actor so callers share one in-flight refresh.
#
#   Closes #142
#
# Enable this template once:  git config commit.template .gitmessage
